comments: ["Having a premium membership, I think the app has way too many fake profiles unfortunately. It's very expensive for what it's worth. The travel mode is very badly designed as you have to remember to go back to a given country to see the likes you got there, it's not all in one place. Finally as a premium user you get one weekly boost for 30 mins otherwise you're drowned in the crowd, basically you get the same level as a non paying member. You have to keep on paying. Greedy company.", "It is a total waste of time and money. It does not matter if you have premium, you won't be receiving any matches at all (I had subscribed to the premium, still the same). It's like a window shopping app where you just keep scrolling and scrolling until you're satisfied without hoping to get anything. For once I thought this app could be genuine and I purchased the premium, but no, if all I had to do was left and right swipe people, I might have as well stayed on Tinder for free.", 'The UI is quite user friendly. But few things which can be improved on. 1. Message notification doesn\'t pop up a lot of times 2. Call notification doesn\'t pop up ever, plus call drops multiple times 3. Filter option doesn\'t work properly, for example if I choose age range 33-36, I still see people of age 23 4. Algo for common interest can be improved specially for best bees feed, I get best bees who want "Something Casual" while my preference is "Relationship"', 'I can not escape the feeling of a jacked up algorithm. One that puts people on the bottom despite their subscription in some sort of "lead with a carrot" business model. That or no one\'s on this app, and the app does not seem to want to take people who have not been on the app in months in the algorithm. Furthermore, there seems to be no quick, obvious, and easy way to end your subscription.', "I used the app for about one year and had a few decent dates out of it. However, as soon as my paid membership expired, literally overnight, I went from having zero people interested in me to 47, of course being prompted to go back to the paid version. Didn't change location or filters during that time, so obviously, they are manipulating the truth and the end user.", 'For an app that requires access to your location, you\'d think they\'d give you an accurate mileage estimate for people near you, but nope they can\'t be bothered to do that. Just saw someone who lives in the next state over from me and, according to Bumble, they\'re 85 miles away from me. However, when I enter the city on Google maps, it gives me a much more accurate mileage: 156 miles. That\'s a 71 mile difference, nearly double Bumble\'s "estimate."', 'The worst of all dating apps. Like Tinder, gives you options from ridiculous distances, especially if youre in rural areas. Most people are visitors from very far. The worst part is once youve swiped left on a potential match they are removed from your likes and you probably will never see them again."you\'ve missed a potential match" forever. Also they put the location at the bottom so you have to scroll the whole profile just to see the distance factor. Overall a very bad experience', "This app is ok but needs work. I canceled my premium. One of the big thing that must be added is letting me know when the last time a person logged on. That way I'm not wasting time on someone who hasn't logged on in a month. That's a waste of a swipe especially a super swipe. Also need to separate straight people from gay. As I have swiped on the wrong person and they get all offended. If these things were fixed I would keep logging in.", "I have emailed support multiple times about transferring my premium subscription from a previously deleted account to my new account and there has been absolutely no response from anyone in support. Unlike other dating apps that allow you to re-instate previously purchased subscriptions without having to email support (that doesn't respond to you anyway), Bumble just really need to sort its issues out.", "Terrible app! you have to pay for basic Things like just to see who liked you you can only see the people that complimented your profile and that's limited, You have to pay for everything like super swipes & to go back if you made a mistake. They took down one of my photos for going against community guide lines but it's a picture of me in a long dress no nudity nothing inappropriate. & whatever preferences youre allowed to choose (age and distance) doesn't narrow down the field", "Still an awful app, I've tried it multiple times and men never see their related matches. We get search results from 97 miles away from people who don't match our criteria. And you can tell even from the blurry images that you never see the people who actually do swipe on you. It's entirely designed to keep you swiping without any actual results. Don't waste your time", 'Waste of time and money, the location of people is totally hit and miss, when you do "match" with someone it is debatable if they are actually real or generated by the app to keep you interested. For an app that is meant to compliment your social circle/find people with similar interests and so on, no one actually talks. Might just stick with the old-fashioned way!', "All the other dating apps I get plenty of matches, but bumble is awful at what it's supposed to do. No matches, and because of the time limit to message you often miss the matches you do get. Pointless app and a waste of time. Edited, after the reply I received more likes than before after I left a review, strange, then they started to get less and Ive just realised the compliment feature has been removed. I think the free compliments were the only thing that made bumble worth using.", "Because you can't filter results by important categories like religion without paying, the app is essentially useless. You are forced to weed through thousands of profiles that aren't close to your value specifications. The profiles layout is also a mess, listing interests in a buckshot-style jumble where things like children, religion, age, location, etc are thrown into the mix randomly and you have to look around more to find it (those should be at the top of the list).", "I think it's more likely to get struck by lightning and win the lottery at the same time than get a match. It's way too easy to accidentally swipe left, and those swiped on can't come back, and the highlights cost 8 bucks each. Like, who even? Fix your app.", "What's the use of having the dating interface if you can't even contact/connect to a prospect without having to pay a bloody fee? And even then, even if you do want to spend on it, the chances of getting catfished is unbelievably high. The aspect of this side of the app is completely useless. I will give it props if you're using it for business networking purposes and works well if that is your ONLY objective. The dating interface is bonkers.", "it's very picky and decisive wanting you to spend money just like any other app. they shouldn't just give the option free to connect with anyone but they should make a lot easier if you want to say hello or block or do what you would like explicit or not. there's filters for everything. just make it all around app that everybody can use. it's 2023 and this is the longest run on sentence I've ever done. but we all know what we're looking for in the beginning and in the end and who may b in middle", 'It\'s just as bad if not worse than Tinder surprisingly. Customer service is 0/10. I can\'t get a hold of any humans to discuss my problems, I\'ve sent at least 10 emails. I get photos randomly taken down because they "violate" community standards according to the algorithm. I\'ve purchased the lifetime membership twice and, like anyone, deleted and reinstalled the app many times, but now I dont have the lifetime membership, and they won\'t fix it. Summary: All dating apps suck.', 'Bait and switched into "subscription". If I wanted to continue after the 1 month trial I agreed to paid for, I would have chosen a less expensive package. I cancelled the subscription and contacted support 20 minutes after charged, I had to open a PayPal case. 2 weeks later Bumble hasnt responsed. Bait and switch auto-subscriptions are theft. Ive lost $60 to this "free" app and have zero dates to show for it, just "content sellers" posting their Instagram and onlyfans.', 'Totally wast of time & Money, I have not received positive responses from the opposite gender. The 30-minute spotlight feature, promising up to 10x matches, did not help. People seem less active, making it challenging to find potential matches. Considering trying other apps, Bumble has not been useful recently. I do not recommend it based on my recent experiences.', "Bumble is useless without a premium subscription. All filters except age & distance are now locked behind a paywall, so rooting through all the bad matches to find someone is a chore. You only get 24 hours to respond to a match, otherwise you have to pay to rematch. And if you accidentally swipe left on someone you do want to match with, you have to pay to undo it. If the woman matches but doesn't start chatting within 24 hours, (Something that happens A LOT) the match disappears completely.", "Not sure how I feel about it. So far I like how the verification process goes and the app runs smooth but been on it for 2 weeks with premium and not worth it. You don't really get as much people due to the fact that the premium is expensive and also the notification when you do get someone doesn't really appear on either the app notification or email. Also anyone you've liked you can't tell if they even seen the like. Definitely needs more work for the cost.", "I like this app, in my opinion it' s very nice but it's just ridiculously expensive. probably the most expensive app I've tried. so I subscribed in different app although I still use the free features on Bumble. Some things could be better. don't like the fact that only match girls can do first move, think that's silly. I've been on a date with a girl and she complained that men never say anything, then I said we can't, first move has to be from girl.", "When you pay to upgrade and it run out. I have found that when you get likes the system doesn't match you with them. I wants you to upgrade. They then timed out and their gone. Don't pay for the upgrade or you'll just have to delete your account like I did. It should be above all, about finding a connection.", 'Having a limit on likes per day isn\'t a bad idea, but this app\'s limit is almost cartoonish. I can\'t spend more than a few minutes per 24 hours swiping without being told I need to pay 3 WHOLE DOLLARS to keep going. It\'s asinine. On top of that, almost everything else is locked behind paywalls. Though I do like that you can list your pronouns without having to first pick "man or woman." But that\'s just basic decency, not a feature', "I've been on Bumble for a few weeks now. Ended up paying for the boost, matched with someone who, for their prompt, asked me to verify my photo. Prior to this I had tried probably 20 times to verify, and was never able to. Yes I tried photos with just myself. Mimicking the pose, hand gestures, and even location exactly, but couldn't verify. Now I'm stuck on the verification screen, I'm being ignored by the support team. 0/5", "To the pros: fairly clean & simple UI, tho a bit outdated. Cons: gps based search, meaning swiping endlessly tons of people in proximity, including tourists & people in the airport and there's no way to filter out. And you have to scroll all way down to find out person is living somewhere else or doesn't disclose. So looks like tinder at this point and more oriented towards finding one night stand nearby. Exhausting & very disappointing experience for me and after a long time trying it, I'm out", "So there is a subscription model for 21 dollars a month, but this subscription does not come with the ability to see who likes you. For that, you'd need ANOTHER subscription 13 dollars more expensive than the regular subscription. To unlock seeing who likes you, you have to pay 35 bucks a month. That's gotta be an accident, right? Why would this feature not be in the regular subscription?", "Don't buy the spot lights!!!! The app will self activate them and email support stopped trying to help! I tried just not being on for a couple days till subscription weekly one was added when I did log on it has already used it and times out! Yes I emailed them and they tried a couple time but stopped helping. Lost 5 so far. And they are not doing anything to help. Very disappointed in you guys. I'm done I've cancelled the subscription and not trying to get your help when you just blow it off.", "It's...ehhh. My issues are the inability to filter out poly/ENM profiles looking for unicorns, continuing to get likes from men when I am a lesbian, the constant message ads and empty notifications, and the high cost of premium. Been using it for a few months now, met one potential person but I'm demoralized. I won't renew my subscription.", 'I tried several times to get my picture verified, including taking a picture, posting it, and then without moving, taking the same picture in the verify area. They still said I could not be verified. I contacted customer service about it, and my app got stuck on the verify photo page and would not leave that page. I then contacted customer service two more times about it and still stuck. It would be nice to at least be able to try the app out.', "Well developed but core functionality is behind a paywall, and there's no incentive to pay for an app that feels dead. Honestly it looks great but actually seeing who has matched you is behind a pricy paywall, so it's a dice roll as to whether two people see each other, and this makes the limited ability to like people (an otherwise good feature) greatly lower the ceiling on chances of matching. People have moved onto other apps.", 'The app needs work on how it recognizes and interacts with phone media. It\'s difficult to get it to recognize videos & it has double standards when it comes to photos and videos. The app allows the most pixelated pictures you\'ll ever see; however, it won\'t let me upload perfectly fine videos due to "low quality" (they\'re not), wrong dimensions (huh?), or not being shot on my phone (really?). So far, it\'s not very user-friendly.', "Swear this app is a con. I have 9 so say 'matches waiting for me'. I just used a boost and spent the full 30 minutes swiping to see if I would get anywhere with any of them (get rid of or properly match with them) and I didn't come across a single one of these people. It is so blatantly a scam just to make people feel like they have no option but to pay to see more etc etc...", "The customer service for Bumble is absolutely terrible!! I have contacted them over 10 times in a two week span and Bumble has not replied to ANY of my inquiries. My account is stuck on photo verification and I cannot access any othet part of my account. I am currently paying for the Premium option as well. Don't use this app - they dont care about you at all.", "Bought premium (little under $9/wk because it was on sale). Was good at first but right now it's not letting me view profiles of people who have liked me (I can see their picture but when I click on them a blank square comes up instead of their profile). Literally the only reason I bought premium was so I could see people who liked me, so it's very frustrating that the feature stopped working. Hopefully it will work again soon. Edit: also not letting me send or view messages right now. :/", 'Very good idea but poor efficiency; is a pity that girls have only 24 hrs to establish a contact... Also, you should put more filters: for example: eyes color, hair color, etc., and stablish options to search by that criteria; for exemple, if I only want to meet people without kids or blonde girls or short (or tall) girls, be able to find those persons easily.', "The premium option is nice, maybe a little expensive for what you get. My issue is that with the premium subscription you run out of people within your filters. But if you're subscription ends you will run out of likes before you run out of people within your filters. Things don't add up properly.", "Even after having premium it doesn't let's text to someone who liked my profile. It clearly showed in best bees match. But it didn't let me text. What a pathetic app. They just want you to keep browsing and keep paying for super swipes or compliments even after buying premium. You will get nothing here. I think they just got some profiles when they launched the app. Might be no longer active because this app doesn't let people text even after liking from both sides.", "Don't recommend, I submitted seven verification photos exactly the way my profile poster was & when I tried to get customer support I've gotten zero response back other than them saying they verified who I am but to try to keep verifying my picture that matches. I paid for the week premium & the app is still stuck in the verification process & will not let me move forward. & they're still trying to charge me of subscription fee. The email I get back from customer service is a auto generated"]

title: WBYF: Dating For Dogs
description:
WBYF (Wanna Be Your Friend) is the official International dating app for dogs. Join us and be part of a happy dog family.
Start connecting with other dog-lovers in your or any location to match, chat - swap pet photos and go on dates. 

MAIN FEATURES
- Profile for your dog
- Meet dogs near you or around the world
- Private messages
- Vote for your favourite dogs
- Today's Birthdays list
- Find puppies and dogs for sale online
- View Lost and Found dogs
- See if anyone else has liked your profile
- Memory page of dogs (This page is "In memory of beloved pets who went to heaven")
- Go on dog dates

FREE TO USE
WBYF is free to download and use.

CREATE YOUR ACCOUNT
Creating an account is easy! Enter a full date of birth and sex of your dog, then start filling in some basic information to create your profile.
summary: Find friends for your dog around you or from around the world

title: Rover - Dog Boarding & Walking
description: Rover is the #1 pet sitting and dog walking app. Get trusted pet care in your neighborhood. The Rover app was created for dog people by The Dog PeopleTM. Through the app, get adorable photo updates, GPS tracking of your dog‚Äôs walk, an easy way to message sitters or manage your business, and a secure way to book and pay. With over 100,000 pet sitters and dog walkers in the U.S. and Canada, Rover makes it easy to book pet care you can trust. PEACE OF MIND ‚Ä¢ 95% of reviewed services receive a perfect 5-star rating. ‚Ä¢ Every service booked on Rover is backed by The Rover Guarantee and 24/7 support. FAST & EASY ‚Ä¢ Contact and message sitters and dog walkers, right from the app. Receive messages from sitters when you're on the go. ‚Ä¢ Hassle-free and secure payments, every time. ‚Ä¢ Get a map of your dog's walk, pee/poo and food/water alerts, and a personalized note from your sitter or dog walker. FOR PET SITTERS AND DOG WALKERS, TOO ‚Ä¢ Send photos, videos, and messages to pet owners with just a few taps. ‚Ä¢ Get paid on the go‚Äîit‚Äôs simple and secure with the Rover app. ‚Ä¢ Seamlessly manage your business, even if you're at the dog park. ‚Ä¢ Enable push notifications to respond faster than ever to booking requests. ‚Ä¢ Create Rover Cards to seamlessly share information with your clients. IN THE PRESS Rover has appeared in: ‚Ä¢ The New York Times ‚Ä¢ The Today Show ‚Ä¢ The Wall Street Journal ‚Ä¢ USA Today ‚Ä¢ ABC News ‚Ä¢ And many more!
summary: Book neighborhood dog boarding, dog walking, pet sitting, and doggy day care.

comments: ["The concept is good and, when I can find a sitter, it's great! The problem is that the availability thing doesn't work very well. The app will let me send a request to someone for the morning who is available only in afternoons. It would be so much easier for me to find someone if matches by available time windows was a thing", "The app it's self is very glitchy. Either not working and shutting down or lagging and making the whole system unusable for several minutes. Customer service is hard to reach out to and get responses from. Though the system is set up to send out quick messages to remind users of its terms of service at any suspect of work being done around the app, they are very slow to respond to concerns brought up through customer service and is difficult to access. All while rising the price", 'The app should display the actual price when searching for sitters instead of the never accurate "starting at" price. I understand the price is based on different criteria but many of them are known ahead of time, for example the number of cats to be watched. This should be accounted for when showing prices. Instead I\'m forced to go into each profile and manually calculate what the price will be.', "Bad app, need much more filters, spent hours trying to find someone. Reached out to three people who said they weren't available even though their calendars fully open. Second, we have a dog who absolutely cannot be around other dogs. You need to have a filter for sitters with and without animals. So that I can eliminate 95% of everyone on the app in order to find those who are actually able to help. Also you can't sort by prices for multiple dogs and an entire stay. Useless", "Great dog walkers, horrible app. There are no filters. People whom are no longer working on the app are still suggested. People you'd like to book again but do not have confirmed availability are suggested. Some require up to three days in advance, though you've indicated that you want to book for the next day, they are suggested to you. Really frustrating and clunky UI. You have to comb through the suggestions for your exact criteria. It shouldn't be so labor intensive to find a walker.", 'I love this app and it is a blessing for me to have a job as a sitter/walker with this app ! I love meeting clients and caring for their pets. But a LOT of technical issues with this app and it is not the easiest to use . They need to show the list of clients pets on the calendar , not just #s of book. Cancelling a booking needs to be more user friendly . It needs to have an Unwalk options if sitter accidentally started a walk timer under the wrong name. And schedule change needs to be simple', "I find this service leaves a lot be desired. Very difficult to resolve issues or even contact customer service directly with any issues. Unless, you don't mind waiting for email responses or being directed to unhelpful automated links that don't resolve the problems. Very expensive and a lot of unreliable walkers and with no accountability for their terrible service. There are some great walkers but few and far between. No weekly or monthly rates.", "I just started using it. It's good so far, but please allow owners to delete messages when not booking with someone. The messages just build up, and I have to sift through to find one I need. Also, having people outside of my address that I need someone to come to is a little deceptive. Other than those issues so far, it's good. I hope those 2 issues can be resolved. ***Even though nothing is booked and it will move to archive I still think the option to delete would be nice to clean things up", "I'm a sitter and I signed up using my Facebook account. When I sign in online it works fine, but when I try to sign in with Facebook on the app it completely freezes. There's no new update, I've waited, I've reinstalled, cleared cache and data, I've done everything I can think of. It doesn't work. I don't want to create a new account after going through the whole application process and already submitting for a background check. So basically, the app is unusable for me", "App needs work: trying to add my cat, and where it asks for adoption date, you can't enter a date. You have to scroll back from the current date. Not only that, but I can't even scroll far enough back to my cat's adoption date. I can get the month, but according to Rover, my cat has been alive too long, and they have greyed out the dates. I am also not alone in thinking the pricing structure is very confusing.", "I am very fortunate to have found an amazing sitter. However, the app needs work. The fees can be a bit outrageous for how poorly the app works. Messages always come jumbled up, and it can crash randomly. Sometimes, I don't get notifications either.", "Took me a bit to get used to because it's different from other apps I use, but it's very convenient and everything is handled smoothly in app. You get alerts when services stop and end, and summaries with pictures.", "It would be nice to get some extended features from the website implemented, i.e. bookmarks, but also better search filters and sorting. I understand Rover doesn't want to favor certain sitters but people do have preferences you cannot take away. Not being able to narrow down the search even further, only makes the process of finding a suitable sitter more tedious. Also, please give the user the ability to cancel requests, I hate looking at aged, pending inquiries to irresponsible sitters.", "Rover makes it extremely easy to find very good pet care services for reasonable prices. While there are pieces of the experience that could improve, like the ability to modify a booking while it's happening or the initial account setup, the overall experience is far superior to going into public listings and ads.", "As a sitter, I've had a mostly positive experience but with some room for improvement on the app. As a pet owner/customer, there is definitely more to be desired. I've sent my suggestions for improvements on both fronts, and their team acknowledged all of the suggestions right away but I have yet to see any implemented.", 'Easy to book. Frustratingly hard to cancel. My dog has issues. booked a sitter and meet up before to make sure it was OK. Both agreed it would not be a good match. I cancelled on Rover. "Rover needs to review this request before we cancel and refund." 6 days later, no response. No option to see status in my dashboard. No live chat to ask. No phone number listed. Googled phone number for human and called. Bad automated responses and a transfer before I got it cancelled.', "At first I liked this app but it became intermittent, it didn't pass on every message to everyone. But the biggest problem: each time we make an appointment, it charges us $3 and our puppy care provider $5!!! Way way too much money for the service. We simply moved to a group text.", 'Overall, very good app. And very helpful people able to look after your pets. The app has a few quirks that could do with making it a little clearer, but other than that, seems good.', "the numbers you supply your employees to text from, I am unable to reply to. my sitters were not getting my texts, and they were looking at me as the faulty communicator. i don't like that. once i figured out that your texting system works one way, I just have had to open up the app each time. it's annoying, but necessary. everything else has been satisfactory.", "Already not liking the fact that I can't log on from my Google account to the app...it tells me to leave, then open a web browser 1st....JUST TO ACCESS THE APP?? ...Thumbs down Rover! Most apps let you create and log in from the app...who wants to go open an https browser if I've downloaded your app to do all of this?? Bad design Rover.", "Great site, easy to use. I think my only complaint is that the fees were hefty to modify a visit and to cancel a day when we were camping and cut short due to weather...both fees applied. Otherwise totally appreciate the service, and appreciate that the changes have to be initiated by the sitter so they don't get screwed over. Good care for my furries!", "Review as a walker - the design of the app is clunky, buggy and quite slow. The sorting/searching of the messaging system is reminiscent of a Moodle forum from 2005. They will spam your email with irrelevant suggestions. The degree of support walkers get is not much at all. As a walker you are quite vulnerable to damage and injury without financial support or recompense from the company. It's useful as a side Hussle... But quite liable to use as a main source of income.", "The Rover app and whole experience is good. I have used it many times for dog sitting and it's been great. However it's becoming just too expensive and I will now only use Rover as a last resort. The latest occasion ended up being ¬£65 for a 1 night stay. That was for someone whose initial advertised rate was ¬£24/night. Too much I'm afraid.", "App is difficult to navigate - it's hard to see your schedule for upcoming walks, as well as invoices and charges. Customer service is non-responsive. They charge both caregivers and owners a fee, yet they don't provide any support whatsoever. I do NOT recommend using this app or the service in general.", "I've been a sitter on the app since 2018 and I am changing my review for a 4TH TIME! AS A SITTER I DO NOT THINK THESE RECENT UPDATES ARE HELPFUL!STOP! The rating service needs to change, go back to private, and be available for sitters to view from the phone app. The calendar immediately needs to STOPbeing updated! After this most recent update where you can now view individual days, if you click on it takes you to a blank screen and two circles which I assume are the bookings but don't show up.", "Finding people on the app that have their timetable up to date is so difficult, people's pricing in search differes from what they have on their profile and best of all there is a 25% service charge per booking to boot! That means ¬£6.25 service charge for a booking of ¬£25....that is after you put in the effort of actually finding a person that has accurate information on or that doesn't mess you around. Do not recommend.", "The app itself is terrible to manage. Doesn't do a good job at telling you what is/isn't booked and what's pending or not pending. If you have a weekly set up, like we do, and need to cancel 1 of the days, you must contact the host and have them cancel for you. Even if you're canceling a Thursday appointment and it's Tuesday. Because the week already started. Which doesn't make sense as to why I need to reach out to the host. Customer service is nonexistent. Looking into daycare away from Rover.", "It's very frustrating that the only way you can contact support for a non emergency is through email. I need to make a modification the day of, and instead of the owner the request went to support. They have not approved the request, nor are they responding to my emails. It would be really helpful if there was a number that could be called to handle this situation, or respond to emails more timely.", "So you'll pay for your membership and then they will take 20% and up everytime you book someone. Then if you take a job and the person pays you cash then rover will deactivate your account and not let you ever get it back. Idk if I would recommend this app. I found one for completely free and they don't take any of your money and it offers more than just animal jobs. Rover support isn't very helpful either.", 'Great easy to use app. I appreciate that you have multiple options for both dogs and cats to either get daily walks, drop-in visits, in-home care, and even housesitting. Our cat is way less stressed being able to stay at home than having to go to the border while we are away.', 'CORRECT THE BOOKING TIMES PROBLEM:: The booking \'time-frame\' has confused every owner that has contacted me. The requirement to select 4 different times doesn\'t work (especially since you only calculate the time from END start to END end). Please remove the "extra" time boxes, which also throw off the calculated care rates!!', 'Rover does not pay the sitters! I have been working for almost a month and, besides charging an obscene amount of fees from both owners and sitters, all the payments keep getting canceled. Funny how to process the clients\' payments, it takes seconds. Edit after developer response: it\'s insanely hard to get support. I\'ve been dealing with this for more than a week and all I get is "update your bank info", "wait 5 business days".', "They have a ton of flakes, the workers rarely have a calendar that is accurate. Part of the problem is you have to reach out to 10 people just to get one and sometimes they cancel at the last minute. There should be some sort of financial penalties for canceling last minute. & often you're just settling for your 5th or 6th option which might be a lot further away from where you live then what would be ideal. I've given up on trying to find a dog walker 0% success on even finding 1 after 15+", "Suggestions in general for Rover, both on app/on desktop: Allowing walkers to adjust available times on individual days. I'm available in the AM on Mondays but not Tuesdays, yet there's no way to display that (easily). Also, clients should be required to rate walkers. So many clients just do not rate, and that prevents new walkers from being discovered/booked. Maybe if this was a feature, the people in previous reviews wouldn't have a hard time finding an active walker.", 'This app is so poorly designed. Users should be able to delete pending requests. Pick up and drop off time ranges makes no sense. Interface is outdated. Every complaint gets the standard bs response but never gets fixed. Spare me the bot response, just fix it.', "I'm happy this service exists but this is one of the worst experiences I've ever had. the user design is flawed and confusing, with only a fraction of the usability that the website has. It's hard to get back to search results, the inbox is divided by purpose instead of most recent messaged being first, and don't even ask me how to change a password because apparently it's not possible even when security risks are present. Literally such a frustrating app design, I hate it.", "I like this app, I use it weekly as I travel for work. Only 3 stars; I have a real issue w/ the update that automatically adds another sitter for you to check w/in the process of booking. If you don't catch it you send a request to a person you don't, doesn't know anything about your pets, then gets mad when you really don't need them because you never wanted them in the first place. If I wanted someone else I would look for someone else. And trying to find & navigate the calendar is horrible.", "Useless app! The most ridiculous user experience. Where do I find my booking? It's not on my calendar. My calendar shows I'm booked, but the color coding is redundant. Two colors to show you're unavailable. Still can't click on what I'm booked for on that day. Go to messenger in the app, can't click on what was booked. You can go all over the app and not find what you're looking for. The client also has a hard time figuring out the app which leads me to have to go find I, and I cant!", 'The app is not user friendly. Have to hunt for the menu to modify or cancel a booking when that should be something that has its own prominent button. Not very well designed.', "This app does not allow you to be flexible with check-in times. If you are going to be out of town and away from your pet for a few days, you must choose a specific time each day for the sitter to check-in, without the option for a time-range. I don't care what time the cat sitter arrives, as long as someone checks in with my cat once a day while I'm gone I'm happy. This company does not want you to have any flexibility. Such a stupid product design choice."]

comments: ["The account setup is great but the app itself functionality-wise is a mess. I can't even like a profile without it telling me that I need to verify my account even though I did it, multiple times via email. It's the same with the video verification as well I submit but then the same page appears over and over. I can't use basic functions, It's because of this that I won't be using this app. There's also a very limited selection as well as I've been seeing the same profiles over and over again.", "I heard good things about this app. I went and purchased the shortest subscription among only 3 choices it offered to handcuff me to in terms of subs. (3mo). I'd have liked a weekly option to try it without the long commitment. There's nothing wrong with the app itself. Only, I keep seeing the same online users over and over. After reaching out to dozens of them not a single one replied. The only good thing I've found is there are no bots. I cancelled the sub but still have over a month left.", 'The app is a complete waste of time unless you are willing to pay their monthly fees to see who liked you or send & read messages. So, unless you pay AND the person you wanted to communicate with also paid for the subscription you will be wasting your time. Also, if you do happen to join, you will see a green dot on a few profiles indicating they have logged on within the past few days. There are very few even when I expand the search criteria. An absolute waste of time.', 'I have been on here 2 months.....I paid to be able to talk and maybe meet someone. I am constantly having to verify myself. No one responds to messages or likes. The profiles for the smartpicks, you can barely see the pics people put up. I constantly have to change my search preferences and no preferences for the smartpicks. Honestly, the app really sucks!!!!', 'The app continuously crashes after about 2 mins of use. Very frustrating! Carousel is a useless tool as it doesn\'t take any of your preferences into account and you can\'t see how far away some is when choosing to "like" or not. If someone lives 500 miles away I wouldn\'t "like" them.', 'So frustrating, who are your developers and ux people??? Has to be one of the worst dating apps in navigation and usage... Same girls keep popping up first so you have to keep scrolling through them to get to the new ones, this is a 10 minute coding fix and no one thinks this is a problem??? And two options, remove conversation and remove connection, what the heck... And then some girls you only get one of those choices even when you have written them... Just horrible quality control', "Same notifications are being shown all the time. In Smartpick, you can't look at photos, only a tiny thumbnail of 1 picture. So how are you supposed to choose and teach the algorithm accurately about what you like?", "Customer service was good when I complained about a couple of things but other than that that's about as far as it goes. If anybody's actually real and close to you they certainly don't want to chat or me. I sent out 67 messages got a response from one. Pay the extra for premium messaging so they could answer me without worrying about it and they still didn't do that. Just like all the others it all comes down to money nonexistent profiles. Pretty much a waste of time.", "It's a free app you pay for... Ots free to download, setup etc then to even message yoi have to pay , the UI is absolute trash. Should not be allowed to have apps this predatory. So after trying it further just seems more and more like 99% if the interactions are fake. If not 30 seconds after I like someone they like back instantly but anyone I pass doesn't like it screams some marketing BS. Also ¬£25PM? For any kind of basic app use? Yeah you need shutting down.", "Set up to keep you swiping, recommends users and hitting the red x does not make them go away so even if you just see the user profile Zoosk will alert them that you're in fact visiting their profile. So it looks like a bunch of people are viewing you. Carousel mode sucks because you have to say yes or no based on one pic and not able to visit their profile, smart pick sucks for the same reason, and the next date live feature is like something from some kind of onlyfans nightmare. DELETED", "This app is not worth it. I tried the 1 month purchase and I am extremely disappointed. No one ever response and the same few memeber for the example keep looking at my profile but nothing more. Hey I might not be the most attractive but come on. No activity anywhere .No one ever online it was a waste of money don't waste your hard earned money on this specific app.", 'The style works well. Carousel as others say, has potential, but broken. Why would I want to meet someone 500 miles away? App needs a search choice on activity, mostly dear in my demographic. Wish I knew how it worked better before wasting money subscribing. WE NEED A SEARCH OPTION FOR ACTIVITY ON APP!', "Hi good day to all. My name is Avion and this is the worst experience that I have had on this app, as a matter of fact, I have an account that can't be erased, thanks to someone who is using it. I have pressed unsubscribed, wrote to customer service, and still it hasn't been deleted. I find it very disturbing that this company has refused to delete my account, that someone else is using, only to their benefit (whose name is Sarah and apparently lives in Houston and I am from the Caribbean).", "I've met some good people on Zoosk, but your experience is probably dependent on your location. The Carousel is the worst. It matches based on pictures, does not filter for distance, and the app counts a Carousel view as a profile view. Otherwise, it's one of the better apps.", "Too many annoying notifications digging for clicks. Don't give you any way to choose which ones you get so you get 9/10 useless notifications just to get the one useful notification. Its like a predatory ad with their click bait. Oh ... and turning off notifications doesn't actually stop them. They just remove the information and send them anyway. Get some better coders.", "My account cannot be deleted. I can only deactivate. This is an absolute disgrace. Who do you think you are, keeping people's data after they've removed consent? There's a vague reference online to having to email the company to get your account deleted. No one should have to do this. Any other app just lets you delete whenever you want in app. Also, it's impossible to find an email address to contact! Oh, and FYI, I'm deleting because the app in general is terrible.", "Can't msg/reply or see msg unless you pay. They edit your bio taking out just the words they don't like. I've X people and still see them pop up. Any dating site that wants the cost of a phone card just to msg someone is unreasonable. They have the option of paying for the year for cheaper per month, but if they did a good job no one should search that long. The view profile is üôÉ scroll every pic before seeing info / bio if there even is a bio.", "Changing my review from two stars to one. Too bad there isn't a zero stars option. DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY ON THIS APP! This app constantly crashes and I have to reinstall every time I want to use it. All they want is your money. I paid for one month and still can't read messages from other users. If I decline or dismiss someone they'll show up the very next day. Most of the profiles that are too good to be true are bots. Don't walk away from this app, RUN!!!", "Horrible interface. Doesn't limit distance or necessarily show distance to potential matches in all is modes. Not very clear. Also seems to nickel and dime you after you have a subscription. Wouldn't recommend at all", 'Issue when you scroll over those who have "Viewed Me" it registers to the other person that you\'ve browsed their profile when you\'ve just scrolled past. This generates confusion as people think you\'re interested in them if you have to scroll past. Please fix this up so that the wrong message is not received.', 'There was no option to chat with anyone without having a paid subscription, so I went ahead & paid for 3 months, just to find out that\'s not the worst part. Men who I "X" out, indicating I\'m not interested in keep popping up & keep messaging me. Some getting increasingly more hostile that I\'m not responding. When I disconnect from matches, they still show up in my search, so I get to look at men who have ghosted me after dates. Overall I\'m displeased.', 'In my opinion, it seems like a scam , I have a team of people who check if these apps are legit , and it seems like some of the profiles are not legitimate. The same , you need to buy credits to chat with people , even when subbed , if you by credits , seem like it either an Ai , or a paid actor that response immediately, please comment if you had similar experience , having to by credits is a red flag lots of sites use the same model , this is all in my opinion.', 'I used to enjoy this service before covid. Now, there are tons of inactive accounts, I know for sure I used to date some of these ladies who are now moved or in a relationship. I wish they required you to long on to keep the account active and disable those accounts who havent login for years. Hardly anyone responds to you. You have to pay just to message anyone or pay for the feature to let people message you back. My area has no members who are active. I felt baited to pay for a subscription.', "It's okay.. I'm truly wishing that the possibilities of dating these amazing interesting guys, just happen to live a very long distance from me... Sad! So, I'm willing to travel a bit.. but it's going to be challenging. I'm hoping this could work out & I find my partner to grow old with, make some wonderful memories.", 'Pretty good app overall. However, Carousel is a totally worthless and distracting but prominent aspect. Who can pick who they "like" without a location? This is after all a "dating app" and if a person lives too far away to "date" what the heck difference does it make? If a member lists the maximum distance they are willing to consider, the app should respect that even if it means there are only a few matches. I can always change my search criteria.', "If I x out someone...they shouldn't keep popping up. Give new people!!! Few glitches have been solved...(6/23) Wish I would have read reviews first. Friend of mine met her husband on here so had to try it. *Click a notification and it doesn't take you to it. *People 500+ miles away! *when you back up on the page it takes you to the home screen rather than who you were looking at.", "It's extremely frustrating to be connected with people so far away. I have my search preference for 50 miles but it still shows me people much farther away. I hate Carousel! You can't see how far they are. I have blocked multiple members because of distance but they keep appearing in my search and also on carousel.", "Yeah, this site sucks. You pay the subscription, but you still have to pay for everything else. You see the same people on your searches. It doesn't tell you if the members even use their account, so it's full of unused accounts. I've seen the same people that probably haven't been on for months. You have to pay to see if someone reads your message. No native american ethnicity choice. The flaws are countless.", 'August 13 2023 So far, this has been a brutal experience. I just joined last night and bought a membership plan. But every time I tried to contact someone, it said, "Subscribe to send." I checked my bank & the payment went through. What the hell?! Now, this morning, I\'m getting messages saying I have to have internet to use the app. Again, what the hell?! I sent an email about the situation, but you guys are taking your sweet time to respond. I\'m so turned off by this! Just give my money back!', "Tried the site out for a month, it would have been smarter for me to flush my money down the toilet! This is the absolutely worst dating site if you ask me and I've tried a few of them. You keep getting interest from women you do not want to get interest from! And you see them over and over and over again. There are far too many things wrong with Zoosk for me to detail, the best advice I can give is don't waste your money or your time.", "Some hiccups sometimes you can't use it freely or are able to see the profiles when is important. Make sure you are talking to a real person, be open to make so friends and who knows. You might be able to find the person that you are looking for!", "Miserable user experience. They charge too much for what you get and constantly ask for more money. There is no way to search for new users without going through the hundreds of users you already have seen. Most users don't respond, which makes me wonder if they are real accounts. Do bot install. Stay away!", "It's not bad however, the amount of fake profiles is unfortunate yet, this is my 3rd time back because out of say 100, 2 that I've met which each turned into a relationship that lasted over several yrs were amazing & worth it. In fact I'm still friends w then after our relationship ended. ü§∑üèª\u200d‚ôÇÔ∏è", "This is about the worst dating app I've used. Hardly any matches in my area. Many of the daily Smart Picks are 100 miles away from me! Those I have matched with don't want to engage in a back and forth conversation. So frustrating!", "Paid for a one month subscription and still denied access to perks of a subscription. Why pay for something when I'm getting the same deal for free? I definitely won't be subscribing again or will I'll be keeping my account active.", 'App is okay. Routinely gives you "views" to keep you interacting with the app though those people may not be actively viewing your profile. The carousel portion is frustrating as you can\'t see the person\'s location and their proximity to you. Lots of "likes" from people way too far away. Met a really good guy on the app and I\'m grateful for that. Watch out for fake profiles/scammers.', 'Terrible app. It constantly states it has no internet connection. It does! All the time. So, I have to uninstall, then reinstall. Absolute pain!', 'WASTE OF TIME AND MONEY! Terrible site. Messages keep failing and being deleted. Site keeps locking up. Customer service is not fixing it. Keeps showing same people even after Ive said no dismiss. Cant block the creeps. Does not work. WASTE OF MONEY! No way to get refund for garbage app.', 'Literally liars. Don\'t fall for it. This app fabricated a message from a profile I liked so I got a message notification. I pay to see the message and it\'s "Thanks for the greeting! Send me a message to start chatting!"', "If you tried to make a worse dating app than this I don't think you could. From fake profiles to delayed messages to would you like to pay extra to see if a message you sent has been read by recipient. Garbage in every way. 0 stars. Designed to keep you paying and paying and paying. Originally a Facebook product. ."]

title: Merge Dogs
description:
Merge your dogs, build the ultimate dog racing team and win the race!

Do you have what it takes to be the best dog racer out there? Start by getting small puppies, then upgrade them into bigger faster dogs and earn lots of money!

Features:
- Over 20 different dog breeds to discover including shiba inu, corgi, golden retriever, pug, french bulldog, chihuahua, poodle, beagle, dachshund, dalmatian, dobermann, rottweiler and lots more!
- Idle earnings. Gain coins even while you are away or offline.

Manage your team of super fast dogs. Start your dog racing team now and become a champion!
summary: Build your doggy team and win the race!

comments: ['The design of everything is very simple and cute. The animations and feel of it is very happy. You do have to wait, but the animations help for the wait time since the animation entertains you as you wait. A very fun game overall. Perfect for people who like achievin', "This game was fun at first but it starts playing you when your about the finish the game like not giving you your money and taking your good dogs and replacing them with bad ones ( for example there are 5 pages and I was on the husky on the 4th page and they replaced it with a dog from the fourth page) which may not seem like a big deal but the higher the dog the more epband money so replacing it so you get less and have to wait months for a new dog This game is just impractical don't waste time", "Starts off fun but after you gather a few dog species it becomes very difficult to move in to the next species. especially because the money you gather while the app is off is limited. Fun but has more potential. I've dropped it now.", 'Very addictive. As a dog person this game is perfect for me. If you are a dog person you should download Merge Dogs! The graphics are great. So many new types of dogs to collect. I have used the 2x speed. It is one of the best money makers in the game. The 5 star review has been earned. Download right now!', 'It\'s ok... a bit confusing at first figuring out what to do and what the purpose is of having the dogs run laps in circles... keep thinking they\'re going to get tired and get thirsty... thought it was going to be more like a "real merge three" game, not merge two or more. I do however enjoy "creating" the new dog species! it is original, but it needs improvements overall. gets repetitive and lacks incentive after awhile. but I think many people would like it with a clear explanation of what it is', "Really good game it gets kind of boring because it's just a loop you get a dog you merge the dog then again. I think it's a very good game though.", "I love everything but could get lil boring rarely adds don't have to pay money it's good üòä one thing though there is bugs like sometimes one of the dogs was tiny and hard to see maybe see what's wrong? I recommend the game though ;)", "This game is amazing! There are rarely ads, and the dogs are super cute! The only thing is that it gets boring sometimes but that's okay! PLEASE download this app!!!", "Alright, so, I really enjoyed this game at first. It was super fun, really cute, definitely addictive. However... I'm about halfway through the catalogue both for the grass track and the snow track, and now it's boring. It takes too long to get to the bigger dogs, since you only get two hours of away time. There's an upgrade for two more but... Do I wanna pay to still barely be able to buy two dogs at a higher tier? There just isn't enough to do to keep it fun. Good for a while tho!", "This game started out lots of fun and I was always excited to see all the new dogs you could unlock but as you get into the later stages, sometimes my best dogs are randomly deleted and replaced, I have been playing for a long while so it takes weeks and months to get a new dog but they keep getting replaced before I can get a new dog, it does it often and it's impossible to progress through the game at this point. It takes away from the cute aspects. Example; Lost my Samoyed for a Dalmatian.", 'This is a good mindless game to pass the time, it helped me fall asleep. A tutorial would have been nice, I played for days before I figured it to click on the dogs and rabbits. The look of the pit bull was disappointing. All the dogs are very happy looking except him. The devs had an opportunity to put the beautiful dogs in a positive light and they took a wrong turn with it. Last, I beat both levels in just over a week, more levels would be awesome. I am uninstalling for now.', 'okay. i love the colours and the art style used! they really compliment each other and make the game enjoyable. i REALLY like the ability to buy certain dogs as you level up!! that makes it a lot easier but still challenging enough to keep playing! one thing i would like would be the ability to purchase outfits for certain dogs, with in game watch to earn ads, and ingame cash from the dogs. overall this game is great ‚úåÔ∏è', "Addicting and fun, until the ads stopped working, except, of course, the ads that provide zero benefits, which also happen extremely often now. I tried restarting the app multiple times. No luck. Fix this soon or I will delete. I already had to skip a bunch of rewards that I can't get anymore because I could have gotten them by watching an ad. Not satisfied at all... :( UPDATE: They sort of fixed the issue. I can get a reward from a video once, then I need to restart the app, so 3 from 2 stars.", 'This game is great! So fun! When i downloaded it at first i was a bit skeptical thinking about how hard it would be to get more dogs when i got pretty far in the game but i actually enjoy the way they set it up greatly! How you let the dogs run to collect more coins. Its creative and a good way to not run out as well as you dont have to buy coins or watch ads for them! üòÅ Love the game! Addicting, easy, and loads of fun!', "The game isn't really challenging for the mind. Buy a dog, for ever increasing prices, or wait for a free one. Let it run on the track to make money. Combine two of same to get another dog, of a higher level. That one will get you the same income as the two old dogs, only faster, so merging dogs is usually worth it. The rest (free dogs, 20% discount, double speed) is click bait, you get something and the designers earn money. But in the ent, it's surprisingly funny and addictive. I quite like it.", 'I love this game the only thing I wish they could improve is how long you have to merge the dogs. Anyways the whole rest of the game is great!üòä', 'This game is amazing and I love it. I stayed up late playing this game!! It is awesome!! I recommend it to whoever is looking at this. If you like offline games... This is for you! All you have to do to get rid of the ads is turn off your mobile data (if you have that) or turn off your interet! Then no ads. It does load, but dont worry. This is a 5 star rating!!! Love it so much. Again you can always get rid of the ads by turning off internet or mobile data. Anyway, thats my review! ü•∞üê∂üêïüêï\u200dü¶∫', 'MAGNIFIC DOG MERGE GAME üêï good work. Thank you! üê© I was about to finish the game, so I uninstall it to restart it, so much it is relaxing and awesome . üíï', "This game was fun but you need to add a tutorial for new player's but it does help me fall asleep.", "its a cute game, and the dogs models are adorable. it has a short, simple tutorial which is nice. I just don't like how long it takes to upgrade to the next dog. it's a slow-paced game compared to most idle games but that's not a horrible thing. the in-game purchases are also a bit overpriced. I love it as a time passer, but I'm uninstalling.", "It's a cute game but it just feels so plain and basic. At least in Merge Planes you could get boosters, etc for the track, and there was a leader board. I don't want to watch fifty million ads just to make my dogs go faster, etc. And they don't even go that fast with the ads. Plus, the ads don't always work. You need to do more to this otherwise boring game.", "It's a cute app, but is it fun? sort of, at your lowest stage it's fun and you merge but soon it becomes into a log on, collect reward, buy more dogs, close app, repeat. I do like that the ads aren't forced but I do watch them anyway. 1 video to double my 2 billion? sure why not. most people won't like this but I do like grind fest games. so it's cute and it's grindy, following the popular trend of merge apps. with not anything else thrown in to spice it up, that's about it.", "The cutest game I've played so far. The game is very simple and really good for destressing. Animation is cute, and I get excited every time I get a new dog. I'm unable to play ads though so I can't redeem other features. But overall the game is just really chill and enjoyable.", 'This is a great game. But I have a problem, my progress keeps getting lost! I was at the level were I unlocked the sheltie but I come back the next day and it is gone, i still unlocked it in the book of dogs but did not have it on the track. I probably wont get a reply or a bot reply I just hope that this problem gets fixed.', 'I wanted to like this game, but there are a few things that turned me off. First of which was the farther I got in the game, the speed in which the dogs speed around the track literally made me sick. Visually it was disturbing and maybe should come with a warning. The second thing is why is the pitbull the only vicious looking design. All the other breeds look super sweet and friendly. I think the designers are perpetuating an unfair bias.', 'Fun game, but a while ago(long time) i had much progress on the game when it randomly crashed and wouldnt open, this went on for a week until i gave up. When it finally let me play it deleted most of my progress. It is now crashing again and im thinking it will do what it did previously, nice app, but please fix it so it doesnt delete progress, or atleast let us save it somehow.(im on latest version so that cant be why.)', "This app is so so cute and fun!! But it has a bug that happened to me twice. I don't know how that happened but it was in the snow place that my fastest dog lost two times. So I have to use more money and it's so hard because of slower income because of the bug. And also the away time says I'll get my income for 4 hours when I don't use the app but it's just actually 4 minutes. I was supposed to earn at least a trillion in 4 hours but it just gives me 50 billion. It's a fun game though. = )", 'Stopped playing it last year because constant crashes made it impossible to play. Felt the urge to play it again and glad to see that the crashes have been fixed! Cute and fun way to pass the time!', "Thia game is an adorable idle merge game, there's enough factors that go into each dog that give the game more depth than expected, and I love that it has multiple worlds or zones that play at the same time. The only thing I think the game is lacking is a more solid active playing aspect, I'd like to see some kind of minigame alongside the idle aspects, but it's still a complete game that is worth your time.", "Like the game as a way to kill time. Got to Pom, and it looked like it was floating? Thought nothing of it and continued to play, only to find that when I got a 2nd Pom, they wouldn't merge. Closed the app and restarted - my 2nd Pom is going and the Pom I have has been taken off the track. This has happened twice now.", "I think that the game was very simple and easy. It was very short thought. You barley got any dogs and most other breeds can be left out. I know it is kinda tricky to find nonpopular breeds of dogs, but I still think it's great. To the game creaters, you should make one with cats and the different breeds also. I think the game was very cute and I enjoyed it.", "well.. I liked this game, it was fun to merge the lil doggos to get more doggos. BUT. After getting over half the doggos in the regular one and almost completing the snow one, the game continuously crashes. I open it and not even 2 seconds later it crashes. Not enough time for me to do anything. It's super frustrating because I'm just so close to finishing it. I put a lot of effort into this.", "It's an easy game to pass the time with. But a few too many ads for my liking. It's ok to have ads for bonus things like the 2x speed but i don't like that one automatically plays for 5 seconds when i close the buy-a-dog screen.", 'The music is greatüëç and very happy üòä! I love the dogs üêï ‚ù§ and they are very cute üòç! the racing is adorable ‚ù§!', "great game, I'm enjoying unlocking so many great breeds of dogs. the ads are a bit much but I'm not even mad considering you can use it for speeding up money, leveling up to a higher breed when using money, but it randomly comes up when you arent clicking anything that would start an ad and it gets quite annoy when an ad appears for no reason.", 'after a while you can no longer watch ads because the dogs are going so fast, so every time an ad tried to pop up, you have to watch your dogs run behind a loading screen for about 5-10 seconds.. I miss the "watch an ad to make them go 2x as fast!" or "watch an ad to get the next level of dog!" so yeah, the process is becoming a lot slower but I still love to poke the doggos. its actually quite addicting considering it gets laggy after a while', "Love it! Super cute and fun! However!!! It doesn't do a good job at conveying some things. Things like the X2 multiplier lasts 2 minutes and 30 seconds. And it doesn't tell you how much your max away is. All it tells you is that you'll get 2 more hours of max away if you pay them real cash money. A bit unnecessarily annoying.", 'I love the game so much it is a cute doggy game I love I how you can get different dogs my favorite so far that I have is my best one the dalmation. I love this game! Update) I would like a "Save" feature. I recently uninstalled (For storage and realized "oh fu-".) Reinstalled and lost my progress. If you could add a save feature so i can reload my work would be nice, If its already there then ;-;-', "Got months of playtime out of this. Simple idler with ROCK SOLID design. Art is adorable, control is intuitive, and lots of dogs means it last you a while. A few design elements raise its quality of life as time goes on: The quick-buy button (not real $) for the smallest dog eventually moves up the ladder as you unlock new dogs, so merge chains don't become impossibly long slogs. And you can always tap the dogs on your track for a little extra speed/cash. My new benchmark for merge-style games.", 'A Great Game! So much fun! At first when i downloaded it looked skeptical and confusing thinking about how hard it would be to get more dogs but when i got a bit far in the game, i actually enjoyed the way it was set up. Love the game, Addicting, easy and lots of funs.']

title: Breedera - Dog Breeder App
description:
Breedera, the top choice for dog breeder cloud software, ensures that every committed dog breeder has all their essential breeding and whelping records, dog and puppy health history, and buyer information in one easy-to-access place. All powered by advanced heat cycle tracking capabilities.

Get started free and:

- Organise your dog, pup, and litter profiles, ensuring you're always on top of the heat cycle stages.
- Log matings, whelping events, and birth weights.
- Expertly track and estimate heat cycles with precision.
- Accurately forecast and countdown to whelping dates using our advanced temperature charts.
- Continuously monitor puppies with insights tailored for a dog breeder.
- Efficiently manage your waitlist, log entries, and contacts.
- Conveniently export, share, and print records or data, a feature highly valued by fellow dog breeders.

All for free!

For the committed dog breeder, delve into the 'Complete Plan' to access Breedera‚Äôs comprehensive health tracking tools, interactive growth charts, and more.

- Log weights and gain critical insights.
- Track and observe temperature changes to forecast imminent whelping.
- Maintain records of vaccines, worming, and flea/tick treatments.
- Design diet routines and monitor impact on adult dog health.
- Keep detailed notes on whelping transitions, growth, and heat cycles.
- Securely upload and store documents and photos, a must-have for any dedicated dog breeder.
- Note: Subscription is required for these features. But rest assured, you can switch back to the Free plan anytime, retaining access to all your vital data.

Receive a FREE 30-day trial for our Complete plan when you sign up.

WE REDUCE OVERWHELM SO YOU CAN...

Focus on what you love:
Relish more moments with your dogs, leaving behind the tedious tasks of updating spreadsheets, heat cycle, and whelping diaries. With our platform, a dog breeder can record on the move, effortlessly tracking puppy health trends and heat cycles using our interactive visual tools.

Stay in control:
For the proactive dog breeder, oversee all your data, past heat cycles, medical treatments, vaccinations, health screenings, and more in a unified platform. Use our tools to predict your essential breeding dates, including our heat cycle predictor, whelping date estimator, and gestation countdown.

Showcase your achievements:
Generate polished health reports to share with vets, licensing institutions, caregivers, or fellow dog breeders. With Breedera, exhibit the full health reports, heat cycle history, progression, records, and profile of every dog, in both digital and print.

WHAT SETS BREEDERA APART?

Flexible Subscription Plans: 
With Breedera, the dog breeder's needs come first. We understand that whilst heat cycle tracking is something you'll always need, not every feature may be required all the time, hence our flexible plans.

Research-driven:
Our collaboration with PhD scholars from Queen‚Äôs University Belfast ensures we're at the forefront of dog and puppy behavioural patterns, focusing on areas like heat cycle milestones.

Trusted by breeders: Breeders globally vouch for Breedera, solidifying its position as an essential tool for the dog breeder community.

Hear from our community:

‚ÄúThis app is what every dog breeder needs. Easy to use, concise, and a joy.‚Äù - White Dove Poodles

‚ÄúThis is the best breeding programme I‚Äôve used.‚Äù - Bowers AKC Labs.

‚ÄúI rely heavily on this app. It keeps me on track.‚Äù - Bearpaw.

‚ÄúThe ability to track puppies and compare weights is invaluable. THANK YOU!!‚Äù - Dayna

‚ÄúI used other breeding software, but for a dog breeder, Breedera tops them all.‚Äù - Stacey.

‚ÄúLove the app. It's essential for my breeding work.‚Äù - Angela.

‚ÄúThanks for understanding the needs of a dog breeder and constantly improving.‚Äù - Amanda

Reach out at support@breedera.com for queries.
